Classwork

1. Install Oracle database (Express Edition)

2. Install SQL Developer.

3. Use SQL Developer to create a CAR table on your machine, as yesterday.

4. Same as before, create a PASSENGER table.

5. Insert data into the columns of these tables.

6. Print out your results.
 
7. Create a foreign key on the CAR table which corresponds to the ID column on the PASSENGER table.

8. Create a foreign key on the PASSENGER table, which corresponds to the ID column on the CAR table.

9. Insert 5 people in the PASSENGER table and place them all in one CAR. Then write a SELECT query which retrieves all the passengers in that one car.

10. Send me a private message showing me what that query was.